{
  "texts": [
    "Function design.",
    "There are already many digital collections of ancient Chinese literature publicly available online, such as Daizhige 5, which is composed of ancient text collections; Erudition 6, which features photocopies of some books, and Jihe 7, which also provides access to ancient inscriptions and rubbings.",
    "However, most of these platforms only offer functions such as full-text search and online reading.",
    "Additionally, there are digital platforms that provide value-added functions such as named entity annotations (Shidianguji 8), character relationship discovery (CSAB 9), and text reuse linkages (Sturgeon, 2019) (Ctext 10).",
    "Nevertheless, none is tailored to accommodate the demands of quantitative analysis over large volumes of textual data."
  ]
}